item.description:
I was just pondering the subject itself. You see, on most subjects that the righties are so angry about, they try to introduce red herrings and other kinds of diversions from the subject so I was just thinking about what the red herring would be on the illegal immigration front. And I just realized that I’ve been duped.

Illegal immigrants take no jobs from Americans. They are creating the jobs they are in and contribute to the economy whenever they shop at the grocery store or buy a car or any of the other things people spend money on to live in this country.

So, I did some researching and it turns out that the vast majority of economists agree with me.

item.title: New Arizona Law
item.dc:creator: danielsangeo
item.description:
You do notice what happened here, right? I never got a response to it. I almost never do. In the rare occasions that I actually GET a response, they half-heartedly agree, then go RIGHT BACK to blaming the immigrant.

I don’t think they actually want to stop it; they just want a nice boogeyman to distract from the real problems. They do it with the “gays”, they do it with the “illegals”, they do it with “abortion”, they do it with “terrorists”. They don’t want to stop any of these things. If they stopped these things, they wouldn’t have a platform to campaign on and beat the left over the head with. And then their true colors come out: They’re corporatists.
